their looks rather than curiosity and interests. Even when their childhood is the most joyful part of our lives, they’re more concerned about their lives in facebook, instagram and so on, than playing with their friends and the environment surrounding them. Like if they were afraid of childhood? Because the way they do their stuff is well organised, smart and make them look as those they already found job which they never do..

Our little girl take lot of image just to look gorgeous and then share them in facebook page. After a picture she take another one because the one we just take is not good as she want. It feels as is she is already using do what she wants for the rest of her life.

It’s ridiculous but yes it becomes something “normal” now. I am thinking that violence and disruptions are what works for solution. 🙂

I wish to say more, but here I have two little girls to look after and take them to school. Maybe later, but probably not as I still don’t understand what’s going on with this generation. It simply, the more they play and spend time with each other, the better they continue to make their society and strong nation.
